What you need to know:

Juventus host Udinese on Sunday before taking on three of the top four this month, with six Serie A fixtures in addition to Italian Cup and SuperCup commitmentsThe two Milan clubs - the only teams apart from Juventus to have won the league in the past two decades - are on top as they look to bring the title back to LombardyAC Milan, without injured Zlatan Ibrahimovic for a seventh consecutive league game, look to continue their unbeaten run at midtable Benevento, as Inter Milan host struggling Crotone